where rmyo is the myoplasmic resistivity (150 U,cm) (13), la is the length of
the LM segment (33.3 mm), and r is the radius of the myocardial cell
(11 mm). A value of 395 kU was chosen for the gap-junctional resistance
(Rg) as the control value as it was identical to the myoplasmic resistance
in an entire myocardial cell (13), i.e., the gap-junctional conductance
(Gg) was 2.534 mS. The radial cleft resistance (Rj) was given by

